<br>
I don't spread this info around in my real life for obvious reasons. The last thing i want to do is be ridiculed.<br>
<br>
Anyway here goes...<br>
<br>
<br>
There are 2 things in my life that Prove to me the existence of God. Now, this may not be God in the conventional sense because I don't fully understand it myself. But there is Something greater than ourseleves. There is something beyond our comprehension that we may never discover.<br>
<br>
You might wonder how the existence of a supernatural concept of God or Something was proven to me. I'll try to explain as best I can.<br>
<br>
The 2 things I spoke of earlier are this:<br>
<br>
1. My dreams<br>
2. Flashes<br>
<br>
I'll explain them both in turn.<br>
<br>
1. My dreams - ever since I was a child I've had odd dreams. As I went through life living in different places and meeting different people, many strange things would be in my dreams. I suppose I was about 9 when I became aware of what was happening. <br>
<br>
Brace yourself...I was dreaming the future. It's happened so many times that i've come to trust it. I have countless times dreamed of where I would be one day. There's never any sound. I see rooms and objects and people. When I dream them I usually have no clue what or where or who they are. As the months go by tho they occur and I remember dreaming about it. For the most part It's nothing terribly specific or important. It's not like I've dreamed that G. Bush would be president, but more like one day I'd be sitting in the living room of a new friend.<br>
<br>
One explanation for this could be that I am simply recalling something that just happened to me and that my brain is confusing it with a dream i once had. That i'm not really dreaming the future, but my mind is mixing it up with the present and past dreams. I would tend to agree with this theory if it wasn't for the flashes.<br>
<br>
2. Flashes - I get these on average 1 per week. I don't have much warning that they are about to happen. Usually only a few moments. I get a strong scent in my nose that's unlike anything. It doesn't compare to food, nature, or anything. I get a solid hum in my mind that doesn't make sound but covers me like a warm blanket. My gut gets tense as though I were sick. This is what happens just before i get the flash.<br>
<br>
Just so you know, most of the time I feel perfectly normal before they happen and I feel ok, if not disturbed, when they go away.<br>
<br>
This is how I feel during the flash. I have to completely stop what i'm doing. If i'm playing EQ i have to steady myself against the wall and chair and look away from the computer while i close my eyes. It's impossible to concentrate on anything but the flash. This may sound weird, but it's like a warm blanket that you can't feel. It's completely disturbing and unpleasant. It is not something i enjoy in the least.<br>
<br>
Now, what is the flash actually about? I'll tell you. I get flashes and images in my mind. I get a rush of feelings and feel things i've never felt at any point in my life. It's extremely odd. I get images and textures of people and places. But it's not like a future. It's like something that I've already experienced. It's like i'm getting some supernatural flashback of a previous life or some insight on something that we just can't normally see or feel. It's extremely hard to put into words.<br>
<br>
When this happens to me I just know. I can't say why or how but i KNOW. What do i know? I'm not even completely certain. It's like i know there is Something other than what we can perceive. There is another demension or God or something. I feel it. I know it's there.<br>
<br>
Usually when these flashes occur everything is perfectly clear to me. For the duration of the flash I know what it's about. I know what i'm remembering or seeing. Once the flash ends I lose my grasp on that. Afterwards I can only remember that I knew what what it was about when it happened.<br>
<br>
It occurs like that every single time without fail. I know that i'll understand for the time of the flash and that i'll lose it when it goes away. It's frustrating.<br>
<br>
For those of you that have branded me a lunatic by now, let me state a few things. I've never done drugs. I don't do drugs. I eat and live responsibly. I treat my body with respect.<br>
<br>
Also i've been to the doctors for years. I've had all sorts of tests done and no one can figure out why the things happen to me that happen. That is also frustrating.<br>
<br>
I don't know what all this means in the big picture. I don't know if i have some sort of insight into things that we have yet to discover. Maybe I am crazy.<br>
<br>
I'll tell you this though. Everything that i spoke of is reality. It happens to me. I can only hope one day I can fully understand it.<br>
